Elders and ward representatives in Garissa yesterday welcomed the appointment of Noordin Haji as Director of Public Prosecution by President Uhuru Kenyatta. The elders led by Mohamud Koriyow said,“We have no doubt he will work diligently as he has done before for this country.” Uhuru nominated Haji last week and he is expected to sail through and succeed Keriako Tobiko, the new CS for Environment. Haji is the son Garissa Senator Yusuf Haji. He has been deputy director of the National Intelligence Service.